rComments: There's quite a bit of reading every week and they are essential for the essays. Although, you can get away with just scanning the main ideas. Go to office hours and ask for help if you need it. Rogoff is a really helpful and caring professor and just wants her students to succeed. Great class overall. I didn't expect it to be so insightful.

there's lots of reading so just make sure to keep up. Essays are assigned every week although they are only 1-2 pages and aren't that bad as long as you figure out how she wants you to structure them. overall the class isn't to hard.

Professor Rogoff is one of the most inspirational and passionate teachers that I have ever had. I am so grateful to have taken her class. She  challenges her students way of thinking, specially how one tends to think ethnocentrically and judge other cultures based on one's own cultural experience or upbringing. Overall, Rogoff is an amazing teacher

Rogoff's lecture style was dull and slow. Obsessed with the idea of avoiding ethnocentrism but believed her way of thinking was the only right way. Texts she assigned were written by her. Go against her ideas in papers and you fail but agree with them and you'll pass. No tests only papers that were about extending ideas of your own based on book

Rogoff is a good professor if you like to be told what to think. Although she encourages students to speak their opinion, she has a way of disregarding it if it doesn't agree with her opinion. The class itself has interesting content. It's easy to get a good grade if you keep up with the essays. Class lectures and pretty dull.

AVOID THIS CLASS! She only cares about her own opinions and uses class to rant about her research without a care for anyone's opposing thoughts.  1-2 Essays due every single week, boring lectures. The only plus is no exams.

Agree with her, get an A. Disagree, and even if you put in a crapton of work the highest you'll get is the B range. She believes her way is right (which is understandable), but doesn't spark interest/creativity in the students for new ideas. I came in interested, I left with huge, huge disappointment. Save your psych seminar for something else.

i quickly lost that interest as the weeks went on. classes were redundant, and often droned on. papers were easy enough, just be sure to take a position she agrees with and then try add your own spin. would not recommend this, especially as a senior seminar, but it's not a difficult class if that's your top priority.

Hated this class. She is very well respected in the psych. world for what she does. However the whole class felt as if she was looking to the students to help HER research. While the point of this class for us to learn how to do our own. Otherwise class was BEYOND easy, so if that is all you are looking for then take the class.

Though Barbra is a charming woman, her class was not quite organized and she was figuring out how the final work should be turned in up until the last day of class. Easy, interesting subject but she spends the whole class discussing ONE of her own studies. Love her, class itself needs a little work. But easy A if you do the weekly papers.

If you're going into this class, be prepared to work! She is extremely dedicated to her students and obviously has a huge passion for the subject, which makes the class great in itself. However, at times, I must admit some topics are left out or ignored because she hasn't studied them in her personal research. But overall, I'd recommend her!

Rogoff's got interesting theories--but she treats them as "fact" and bases the entire class around her book and her own ideas. Weekly essays are tedious and don't really have anything to do with helping you "learn"--you just repeat back what her book says to her to get a passing grade. If you're really curious, just read the book; avoid this class.

Rogoff has good ideas, but she doesn't explain them well. There are weekly essays that are pretty easy as long as you tell her what she wants to hear. She is not very clear though. There are no tests. She isn't a great lecturer either and class is boring as hell. I wouldn't recommend her...

Rogoff is one of those professors that comes to class and brags about her research and doesn't really care if you learn at all. Her essay instructions are very vague and I rarely have a good idea of what kind of grade I'll get. It doesn't help that she doesn't give a letter grade either. Just agree with her in your essays and you should do fine.
Doesn't explain her concepts well.

She's nice, but not my favorite professor. The first month and a half of class we did nothing but talk about how to improve the papers we wrote weekly. There was absolutely no discussion of the book, or the cool video clips we'd watch. The TA was a more effective teacher. The class was worth it, but I just wish less time were spent on the how to's.

i just skimmed through the chapter, found something i wanted to write about, took it to my TA's office hours, got revision comments, made the revisions, took it to class, got a good grade, and then went about my business. worthless class, easy A if you figure out how to work the system.

Despite the neverending weekly essays and assignments, I really got a lot out of the class.  The topics covered were VERY interesting and lecture really explained the studies and topics.  Getting involved in optional presentations and discussions really made this class worthwhile.  Trust me, look past the amount of work, and you will enjoy it.

I liked the idea put forth in her book. I was slightly annoyed by the homework assignments, we got to write about interesting subjects and i received good feedback, but i never got a chance to revise or make papers better. The papers seemed to be about quantity and not quality.

Lectures are a complete waiste of time.  Writing an essay everyweek based on the contents of her book was tedious.  Thought it would be an interesting and somewhat fun class-I was wrong.  As far as writing, do feel my writing skills improved although I feel she did not clarify what she expeted.  It really is trial and error.

This class is extremely boring and tedious. Writing at least one essay a week is time consuming and the grading is rediculous (i spend the same amount of time on each essay and never know what i'll get). Lecture is completely worthless since all she does is repeat her stupid book. Thank heavens I have a nice TA.

The most boring class I have evere had.  The teacher is nice, but she doesn't give grades till the end of the quarter.  Attendence is manatory, so I bring something to read, or my lab top so I don't go crazy from boredom.

She claims to be teaching us how to write and clearly express our ideas, but is unclear herself.  She reads us example papers as though that alone will help the quality of our writing.  She teaches to us like we are 3rd graders.  Since she wrote the textbook she has nothing to say in lecture, which makes it tedious and frustrating.  No good.

I agree with that other guy in that I feel like she really doesnt give a**** about me because i'm not culturally intersting enough.  Also, it seems like all she wants us to do is to repeat her stupid, nonsensical book back to her, and she certainly refelects that in the grading, although she says she wants creative and innovative thinking.

I'm white and felt like she couldn't have cared less about me. I felt the "tough love" routine for my first offense was unneeded. Racial Backlash was in full effect and supported by Rogoff. I was put down, made to feel I was less important/valued and was often made to feel I was a **** and the cause of racial issues by students and professor.

A brilliant, oft-cited woman.  Her teaching style is to be sweet, which can sometimes lead to a slightly disorganized class.  yet the speakers she brings in are great, and if you are going into the Psychology field it would be good for you to get to know what one of the great minds is thinking and tlaking about.
Rogoff is one the best psych teachers you can find. She's very demanding, but her class is worth the effort.
boring as all hell

Take a class with Barbara! Her work is so innovative and interesting, you won't think about things the same way. Her book was extremely interesting, & although the class meetings could have been  more exciting (she's anal about logistics), I enjoyed it.
she is one of the most intellegent people i have met, the best part about dr. rogoff is that she is so aproachable.  great class and great professor!

She is very intelligent, but lacks gusto in the classroom. Her book was amazing but she was a terrible teacher. Her lectures were like going to a writing tutor. I was a little disappointed... Regardless her book was very interesting.

This was the most wonderful class I have taken at UCSC.  Professor Rogoff is very inspirational and sweet.  She really welcomes diverse opinions and challenges your abilities.  Lots of reading and writing essays, but great class!!!
very interesting and nice and fascinating, a lot of writing.
